ted_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:22.210017690Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:29.470416826Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:57:37.332066964Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:58:37.607802571Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:23.141843815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:58:07.476650532Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":342,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: repository docs and redesign notes must explicitly explain event taxonomy, heartbeat semantics, filtered subscriptions, replay-to-live transitions, and how operators or agents tell healthy quiet from broken quiet.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:07Z"},{"id":349,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-docs follow-up: the refreshed docs must clearly distinguish live snapshot, raw event replay, incident replay, and bounded as-of inspection, including when each is appropriate, what limits apply, and how degraded or partial history is explained to operators and agents.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:29Z"},{"id":358,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: docs must clearly explain what ntm redacts, when it emits safe previews, how disclosure markers should be interpreted, and why hidden evidence is still actionable rather than silently missing.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:26Z"},{"id":372,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: docs now wait for 7.3 because operator and contributor docs should describe the richer registry-backed consumer metadata, boundedness hints, and follow-up drill-down semantics as shipped, not document a partial pre-metadata state that would immediately drift.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:48Z"},{"id":374,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: docs now explicitly wait for schema goldens, registry/discovery tests, and disclosure-control verification so repository documentation points at real checked-in examples, real discovery output, and verified redaction behavior rather than documenting an intermediate state.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:59:44Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","title":"robot-redesign/validation: remove legacy robot assembly paths and dead code","description":"Delete or replace the obsolete assembly paths, duplicate renderers, and dead legacy scaffolding that become unnecessary after the redesign is in place. This task exists because leaving the old paths around would preserve exactly the ambiguity and drift this plan is meant to fix.","design":"The cleanup should remove duplicated surface assembly logic, stale helpers that bypass the shared projection model, and discovery code that no longer reflects reality. It should only proceed after unit, integration, benchmark, and E2E coverage are green and docs/examples clearly identify the new path as authoritative.\n\nThe goal is not aesthetic tidiness; it is preventing future contributors from accidentally reviving the wrong architecture.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the old robot assembly paths are no longer active or misleading, the new path is the one obvious way to build robot outputs, and the automated unit, integration, benchmark, E2E, docs, and example stack points only at the new architecture.","notes":"Cleanup is part of the architecture work, not an optional polish pass.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:30.465593071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:47.257956813Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cleanup","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:30.465593071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:37.522173878Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:5